"n.弯路；绕行之路 【英】 n.弯路 (a roundabout way)；绕行之路 (a route used when the direct or regular route is not available) 【记】 de+tour(旅行，走)→ 绕着走 【例】 They made a detour to avoid the busy center of the town. n. 弯路; 绕行的路(一条代替干道的临时使用的路) 【记】de坏, tour旅行－旅行的不爽, 因为绕道了. 【类】detour: route = digress: topic 绕路而行偏离路线 = 偏题偏离主题 【记】de 否定 + tour 旅行；没法旅行，why?前方绕路；tour 来自turn，也有turn的意思,转一圈 detour (n.)  1738, from French détour, from Old French destor ""side road, byway; evasion, excuse,"" from destorner ""turn aside,"" from des- ""aside"" + tourner ""to turn"" (see turn (v.)). detour (v.)  1836 (intransitive); 1905 (transitive), from detour (n.). Related: Detoured; detouring."
